A diagnosis to determine the cause will include obtaining a medical history and assessing the symptoms. Treatment is not always necessary.<ref name="nhs">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhs.uk/chq/Pages/977.aspx?CategoryID=118|title=What causes a woman to bleed after sex? - Health questions - NHS Choices|last=Choices|first=N. H. S.|date=2018|website=|access-date=2018-02-04}}</ref>
== Causes == Vaginal bleeding after sex is a symptom that can indicate: * [[pelvic inflammatory disease]]<ref name="nhs" /> * uterine disease<ref name="mscape" /> * [[chlamydia]] or other [[sexually transmitted infection]]<ref name="nhs" /><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=W-5kAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA423&lpg=PA423&dq=Postcoital+bleeding+men+anal&source=bl&ots=dNVlutnX3P&sig=WFi4e1vNMJTlezYWc1Cf7CNfYvU&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVt7qfpJTZAhWK2VMKHUbGAmc4ChDoAQhJMAk#v=onepage&q=Postcoital%20bleeding%20men%20anal&f=false|title=Davidson's Principles and Practice of Medicine E-Book|last=Walker|first=Brian R.|last2=Colledge|first2=Nicki R.|date=2013-12-06|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=9780702051036|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h65BJiYvt_oC&pg=PA441&lpg=PA441&dq=Postcoital+bleeding+men+anal&source=bl&ots=HvDptyHCr4&sig=KHznydYEdmTTL9QWvzZRzyos44A&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiVt7qfpJTZAhWK2VMKHUbGAmc4ChDoAQhNMAo#v=onepage&q=Postcoital%20bleeding&f=false|title=Hutchison's Clinical Methods,An Integrated Approach to Clinical Practice With STUDENT CONSULT Online Access,23: Hutchison's Clinical Methods|last=Drake|first=William M.|last2=Hutchison|first2=Robert|date=2012-01-01|publisher=Elsevier Health Sciences|isbn=0702040916|language=en}}</ref> * [[atrophic vaginitis]]<ref name="nhs" /> * [[childbirth]] *inadequate [[vaginal lubrication]]<ref name=":2" /> * benign [[Polyp (medicine)|polyps]] * [[Cervical ectropion|cervical erosion]] (inflammation of the cervix)<ref name="nhs" /><ref name=":2" /> * cervical or [[vaginal cancer]]<ref name="nhs" /> * anatomical abnormality of the [[uterine malformation|uterus]], [[vaginal anomalies|vagina]] or both.<ref name = mscape>{{Cite web|url=https://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/412468|title=Postcoital Bleeding in a Premenopausal Patient|last=|first=|date=|website=www.medscape.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20020415190326/http://www.medscape.com/viewarticle/412468|archive-da